    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-22T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-22T21:00:00-05:00" n="463"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d463">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/22326: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hibbard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-22T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 22, 1942—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>166. Your 198, June 18, 5 p.m. War Department requests that Liberian Government
                    be informed that no bombing planes are available for assignment to Roberts Field
                    at present. United States aircraft will arrive in Liberia in adequate numbers as
                    soon as training of unit is complete. Meanwhile arrangements have been effected
                    with the British to provide air patrols in addition to which a certain amount of
                    anti-aircraft equipment is en route to Liberia.</p>
                <p>For your personal and confidential information it is not expected that the United
                    States air unit referred to will have completed its training, which includes a
                    course in dive bombing, before next fall.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
